plan journal describing one-sentence distillations many things he had learned about programming over his career epigrams have been widely quoted he remained at yale until his death publications publications selection introductory course computer programming with robert t braden view programming languages with bernard galler introduction computer science software metrics analysis evaluation with frederick sayward mary shaw about alan perlis denning peter j may alan j perlis—1922–1990 founding father computer science separate discipline communications acm doi101145/78607214943 cheatham thomas algol session history programming languages pdf new york ny acm press p doi101145/8000251198357 retrieved references ulf hashagen reinhard keil-slawik arthur l norberg history computing software issues p26 national academy engineering alan jay perlis memorial tributes vol p168 computer science quotations for listing his talks lectures 1951-1988 see alan j perlis papers 1942-1989 charles babbage institute university minnesota minneapolis external links wikiquote has quotations related alan perlis oral history interview with allen newell at charles babbage institute university minnesota minneapolis newell discusses development computer science department at carnegie mellon university including work perlis raj reddy growth computer science artificial intelligence research communities alan j perlis papers 1942-1989 charles babbage institute university minnesota minneapolis v t e m turing award laureates alan perlis maurice vincent wilkes richard hamming marvin minsky james h wilkinson john mccarthy edsger w dijkstra charles bachman donald knuth allen newell / herbert simon michael o rabin / dana scott john backus robert w floyd kenneth e iverson tony hoare edgar f codd stephen cook ken thompson / dennis ritchie niklaus wirth richard karp john hopcroft / robert tarjan john cocke ivan sutherland william kahan fernando j corbató robin milner butler lampson juris hartmanis / richard e st